From f6ebe8a7363acc4914ac18d9d5d0e86f504765a4 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Mario Limonciello <mario.limonciello@amd.com>
Date: Sun, 27 Jul 2025 17:54:55 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] drm/amd: Sanity check custom brightness curve data points
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

[Why]
The Zotac Zone has custom brightness curve support in it's firmware,
but it has some problems where values don't increase monotonically.

For example data point 27 has a random input signal value of 108 even
though the luminance is otherwise monotonic:

🖴 Count[26]  Luminance Level = 0x34  Signal Level = 67
🖴 Count[27]  Luminance Level = 0x36  Signal Level = 108
🖴 Count[28]  Luminance Level = 0x38  Signal Level = 71

[How]
Add a sanity check when the ACPI method queries the data points
to ensure they're all monotonic.  If they're not, disable advertising
custom brightness curve data points to the rest of the driver and
show a `Firmware Bug` message.

Reported-by: Philip Müller <philm@manjaro.org>
Signed-off-by: Mario Limonciello <mario.limonciello@amd.com>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_acpi.c | 14 ++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 14 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_acpi.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_acpi.c
index f5466c592d94..160c23c22c84 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_acpi.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_acpi.c
@@ -398,6 +398,20 @@ static int amdgpu_atif_query_backlight_caps(struct amdgpu_atif *atif)
 	memcpy(atif->backlight_caps.luminance_data,
 	       characteristics.data_points,
 	       sizeof(atif->backlight_caps.luminance_data));
+
+	/*
+	 * Sanity check the data points to ensure both input signal and
+	 * luminance increase monotonically
+	 */
+	for (int i = 0; i < atif->backlight_caps.data_points - 1; i++) {
+		if (atif->backlight_caps.luminance_data[i].input_signal >=
+		    atif->backlight_caps.luminance_data[i + 1].input_signal ||
+		    atif->backlight_caps.luminance_data[i].luminance >=
+		    atif->backlight_caps.luminance_data[i + 1].luminance) {
+			DRM_ERROR(FW_BUG "Invalid luminance data, disabling custom brightness curve support\n");
+			atif->backlight_caps.data_points = 0;
+		}
+	}
 out:
 	kfree(info);
 	return err;
-- 
